caption:
Table 3. It can be seen that our method achieves significant 
improvement in precision, which is 5.43% higher than the 
best result of previous methods. As for the results of recall, 
CB (common-sense based method) performs the best and 
reaches 71.3%. However, its precision is quite low, resulting 
in poor performance in F-measure. Finally, our method out-
performs the state-of-the-art method ConvMS-Memnet by 
2.87% in F-measure. This shows that our model can better 
identify emotion causes by using text content, relative posi-
tion and global label information reasonably.
